    "client_msg_id": "bdb8ec5e-c061-400d-bcca-58324a011ff8",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Ugh, it looks so cool (and htmx too), but I have a visceral negative reaction to any programming language that tries to look like English sentences. How irrational am I to think that will necessarily lead to doom somehow? Is there perhaps a systematic way to make sure it parses predictably while still having the writability benefits of resembling natural language? Is that even a problem in practice?",
    "user": "U016VUZGUUQ",
